        "timestamp": "2019-12-04 08:07:00.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nI still would like to discuss the user scenario, please don't merge it just yet\nI'll post my comments later today",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "3a1586905e8e3770dc55ac13f6cba371408cc322",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 653,
          "name": "Ofir Sonsino",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "ofirson@gmail.com",
          "username": "os0695"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-12-05 10:11:13.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nSatoshi can you please explain the use case?\nWe agreed that required properties are actually required at instantiation time only, not in design. Why not setting the required:true on service inputs instead of the VFs models?",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "867d529254a98c1fae18199dcdffe433d7078f10",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 5233,
          "name": "Satoshi Fujii",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "fujiisa24@gmail.com",
          "username": "s4fujii"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2019-12-09 10:25:34.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nOfir,\n\nIn MDONS use case, a service itself has properties\n(means SELF properties, not coming from VFs/CPs)\nand we need to set required=true for some SELF properties then declare service inputs.\n\nI think basically service input should inherit definition (such as name,\n description, type and required) from property\nso my thought is that user sets required when they add SELF properties,\nand all definition including 'required' are copied from property definition\n when user declare service inputs.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "f9bb7661b3b06e6b9f0b7c843d142c3dfaedbfaa",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 653,
          "name": "Ofir Sonsino",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "ofirson@gmail.com",
          "username": "os0695"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-12-16 11:24:58.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI asked our UX and product team;\nWe think it would be more clear to the user if the \"required\" field will be a new column in the inputs tab (for services only), because it's only for run time.\nSo we need to make sure there's no change in resources (VF or PNF) behaviour, and move the checkbox to the inputs tab instead inside add property modal.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "665ad77841ded47ba69cb3d735616dba61b153ed",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 5233,
          "name": "Satoshi Fujii",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "fujiisa24@gmail.com",
          "username": "s4fujii"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2019-12-16 13:04:51.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI understand.\nI'll re-design the UI to do so.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
